  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increasing access to justice in rural Cameroon</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Our project began life in 2008 after several outbursts of mob justice in Southwest Cameroon. For the past four years we have been employing a long-term strategy, collaborating with rural communities to increase the capacities of their traditional councils. Our work ensures that there are more effective forums of justice available to the poorest in society, so that individuals will never again be encouraged to turn towards mob justice.</narrative>
  </description>
